 lap and pull out your wallet, opening it up and see a few photos come out. One was of you in your older rally car, smiling the same smile you did in the picture Lexie pulled out. You needed the money, so you pull the blanket off of you and get off the couch.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“I&#039;ll be back.” You tell her with a smile.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">30 minutes later</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">	You make it to the sign up office, which had 2 cars covered with at least a foot of snow in the parking lot. You stop the snowmobile and make your way to the door, which has 2 sleeping bags on the floor. You knock on the door and one of the bags moves, a wolf exiting the bag. He looks at you curiously before getting up and opening the door.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“We&#039;re closed man, you looking for shelter?” He asks.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“It&#039;s not 10 PM yet.” You tell him. “I&#039;m here to sign up for the rally.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">	He groans and lets you inside as you take off your heavy coats. When they&#039;re off, you&#039;re escorted to a sign up area. A very cold looking fox is sitting there, covered in a blanket and a space heater next to him.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“You stuck here too?” He asks.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“No, I&#039;m here to sign up for the rally.” You reply. “You need a ride home? I have a snowmobile if you do.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Nah I live 20 miles away. No coat or helmet either.” He replies. “Just sign on this sheet.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">	You take the clip board in your hand and sign your name. The fox takes the clipboard back and his ears fold down on his head.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“No way.” He says. “You&#039;re him!”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“What?” You ask.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Daniel Fletcher! You&#039;re THE Daniel Fletcher!” He yells excitedly. “I&#039;m a huge fan! I used to watch you race when I was a kid!”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“A kid? How old are you now?” You ask.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“17!” He replies excitedly. “I&#039;m Hugh, it&#039;s a pleasure to meet you sir.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Well, you&#039;re only 4 years younger than I am, so, uh, hello.” You say, offering your hand.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">	Hugh shakes it excitedly, his tail wagging from side to side as you smile graciously. You never knew you had fans.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Whoa, I thought you were in your 30s!” He says. “That&#039;s so cool!”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Hey, could you do a favor and keep the listing a secret?” You ask. “Don&#039;t go telling reporters I&#039;m gonna be there. I have stuff going on and I don&#039;t want news reporters at my house.”</div></li><li clas